    <abstract id="aspace_3eaa5059e290ccb0459e3f0c36f1872c">David Mates served as a lieutenant in the Abraham Lincoln Brigade during the Spanish Civil War, and later served as commander of the San Francisco (Bay Area) Post of the Veterans of the Abraham Lincoln Brigade (VALB). He also served on the VALB National Board. This collection consists largely of correspondence received by Mates in his capacity as commander of the Bay Area Post.</abstract>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_8487da8ee3d46ae0b41d37aa23cb4869">Materials are primarily in English, with a limited number of materials in Spanish.</langmaterial>
  </did>
  <bioghist id="aspace_5ca38a58a95d2e6c4594fbbbd8bf87e9">
    <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
<p>David Mates served as a lieutenant in the Abraham Lincoln brigade during the Spanish Civil War.  Born in New York, he was a labor organizer in Detroit before serving in Spain. After the Civil War he lived in Chicago and Detroit, where he was an organizer for the United Electrical Workers and a Communist Party activist. Later in life he lived in Palo Alto, CA, and served as commander of the San Francisco (Bay Area) Post of the Veterans of the Abraham Lincoln Brigade (VALB). He also served on the VALB national board.  He died in 1977.</p>  </bioghist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_47e266f3968bb0f604eec1f3c24e60d4">
